HACKATHON TERMS AND CONDITIONS

1. ELIGIBILITY
   - Open to all developers worldwide
   - Must be 18+ years old or have parental consent
   - Employees and immediate family of Huitzo Inc are ineligible for prizes

2. SUBMISSION REQUIREMENTS
   - All submissions must be original work created during the hackathon period
   - Submissions must use the Huitzo SDK
   - Code must be shared via GitHub (public or private repository)
   - By submitting, you grant Huitzo Inc permission to showcase your work
   - You retain all intellectual property rights to your submission

3. PRIZES
   - Prizes will be awarded at Huitzo Inc's sole discretion
   - Prize amounts: Best Pack ($400), Most Creative ($250), Most Business Friendly ($250), Worst Bug Found ($100)
   - Prizes paid via PayPal, Venmo, or bank transfer
   - Winners announced within 7 days of hackathon end (March 3, 2026)
   - Taxes are the responsibility of winners

4. JUDGING CRITERIA
   - Best Pack: Overall quality, functionality, creativity, and polish
   - Most Creative: Novel use of Huitzo features, unique problem-solving
   - Most Business Friendly: Practical business value, ease of use
   - Worst Bug Found: Severity, reproducibility, impact

5. CODE OF CONDUCT
   - Be respectful in Discord and GitHub interactions
   - No harassment, discrimination, or inappropriate content
   - Violations may result in disqualification

6. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY
   - The Huitzo SDK and platform remain property of Huitzo Inc
   - You retain rights to your Intelligence Pack code
   - Huitzo Inc may showcase winning packs in marketing materials

7. WARRANTY DISCLAIMER
   - The Huitzo platform is provided "as is" without warranties
   - Huitzo Inc is not liable for bugs, data loss, or service interruptions

8. CHANGES TO TERMS
   - Huitzo Inc reserves the right to modify these terms
   - Changes will be announced in Discord and via GitHub

9. QUESTIONS
   - Contact: hackathon@huitzo.com
   - Discord: https://discord.gg/huitzo

By participating in this hackathon, you agree to these terms and conditions.
